 Delivery Processing System for Producer Cooperatives
 DPS allows remote supply chain transactions to be captured and transmitted
more efficiently, using cell phones. This allows the cooperative to track
specific deliveries (for product differentiation and meeting international
traceability regulations), monitor remote inventory levels, respond to
customer
requests and document the price that was paid to the producer, useful for
fair-trade certification, and for collecting real-time transaction data.
 See:
<http://people.ischool.berkeley.edu/~parikh/projects/CAM/projects.html%20>ht
tp://people.ischool.berkeley.edu/~parikh/projects/CAM/projects.html=20
