            <br>
            <br>
            <b>Delivery Processing System for Producer Cooperatives</b><br>
            DPS allows remote supply chain transactions to be captured and =
transmitted=20
            more efficiently, using cell phones. This allows the cooperativ=
e to=20
            track specific deliveries (for product differentiation and meet=
ing=20
            international traceability regulations), monitor remote invento=
ry=20
            levels, respond to customer requests and document the price tha=
t was=20
            paid to the producer, useful for fair-trade certification, and =
for=20
            collecting real-time transaction data.<br>
            See: <a
href=3D"http://people.ischool.berkeley.edu/~parikh/projects/CAM/projects.ht=
ml%20"
target=3D"_blank">http://people.ischool.berkeley.edu/~parikh/projects/CAM/p=
rojects.html=20
            </a><br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <b>Tanzania Federation of Cooperatives (from ICT Update)</b><br>
            Tanzania Federation of Cooperatives Ltd is the national Coopera=
tive=20
            Umbrella Organisation that promotes, serves and coordinates the=
 development=20
            and prosperity of all Cooperative societies in Tanzania Mainlan=
d.=20
            TFC was established in December 1994 as an autonomous, non-gove=
rnmental=20
            and non-partisan body that is member owned and managed in the s=
pirit=20
            of internationally recognised co-operative principles and value=
